<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1436,151,1023]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,344,298,323]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" reason="1">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Body metallic green with a short yellowish pubescence, denser on pronotum; abdomen orange with last segment and apex of penultimate dark green metallic; antennae and mouthparts, including maxillary palpi, yellow-orange; fore legs yellow-orange; meso- and hind legs black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1436,151,1023]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
Head sub-squared with protruding eyes. Maxillary palpi modified with palpomeres II–III wide, flattened and curved; IV stout (about 2x as long as wide), weakly flattened and gradually widened from base to apex (
<figureCitation box="[1334,1423,446,470]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1418,1441]" captionTargetBox="[177,1426,220,1378]" captionTargetId="figure-611@13.[151,1436,193,1413]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male right maxillary palp, dorsal view: for lettering refer to caption to Fig. 1. Scale bars = 1 mm (1: C–E, G–J, L– R, Y, AA–AC; 2: B, F, K, S–T, X, Z; 3: A, U–W)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5286901" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5286901/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
). Antennae strongly modified with antennomere I bearing a short and pointed protrusion on the external side and dorsal keel narrow and very high, apically fringed; II–VIII variously expanded and shaped; IV with a narrow, long and curved expansion on dorsal side; V with a long and narrow expansion on dorsal side; IX very swollen and transverse (
<figureCitation box="[280,368,593,617]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1865,1888]" captionTargetBox="[158,1411,193,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-144@12.[152,1437,183,1834]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male right antenna, lateral view: A, C. schreberi; B, C. martae; C, C. ephesica; D, C. prevezaensis; E, C. festiva; F, C. graeca; G, C. malatyensis; H, C. albopilosa; I, C. longiseta; J, C. barthelemyi; K, C. vahli; L, C. scovitzi; M, C. latreillei; N, C. adamovichiana; O, C. confusa; P, C. azurea; Q, C. turcica; R, C. muehlfeldi; S, C. schaefferi; T, C. prochaskana; U, C. dahli; V,C. bernhaueri; W, C. simplicicornis; X, C. gloriosa; Y, C. rapillyi; Z, C. marginiventris; AA, C. macedonica; AB, C. kunzei; AC, C. bodemeyeri. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5286897" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5286897/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1436,151,1023]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
Pronotum elongate with a long and deep medial line. Protibiae modified with a very high and flattened dorsal keel, apically curved (
<figureCitation box="[400,490,667,691]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1639,1662]" captionTargetBox="[166,1405,234,1601]" captionTargetId="figure-156@15.[151,1436,193,1618]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 4. Male right protibia, lateral view: for lettering refer to caption to Fig. 1. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5286905" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5286905/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). Protarsomeres dorso-ventrally flattened; I–IV widened on the external side; V distinctly angularly widened on the internal side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1436,151,1023]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
Last abdominal sternite bearing two very long laminar expansions, about as long as the whole last abdominal segment. Gonostyli, in lateral view, slightly curved, with apical lobes dorsally directed, swollen and close to each other in dorsal view. Apex of aedeagus rounded; aedeagal hooks equal in size. Sclerotised hooks of endophallus small and distant from each other, equal in size, the apical pointing outwards and the subapical backwards (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1968,1991]" captionTargetBox="[181,1410,213,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-61@17.[176,1412,193,1924]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 6. Male external genitalia (from left to right: tegmen, dorsal and lateral views; aedeagus, lateral view): for lettering refer to caption to Fig. 1. Scale bars = 1 mm (1: A–E, H, L–M, R; 2: F–G, I–K, N–P, S–T, X–Y, AA–AC; 3: Q, U–W, Z)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5286911" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5286911/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1436,151,1023]" box="[199,999,924,948]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Female. Not distinctly modified. Refer to key for diagnostic characters.</paragraph>
